did.abstract: Joey Bishop started his career as a nightclub comedian. He was featured on The Joey Bishop Show and The Joey Bishop Show (late night talk show), and acted in various motion pictures, including Ocean's Eleven and Valley of the Dolls. In the 1960s and 1970s, he also performed regularly with the Rat Pack. The collection consists largely of records pertaining to The Joey Bishop Show (late night talk show) and is made up of guest research files, guest contracts, weekly lineups, and financial records. Also included in the collection are a small number of scripts representing Bishop's other television projects.

bioghist.head: Biography/History
bioghist.p: Joseph Abraham Gottlieb, later changed to Joey Bishop, was born February 3, 1918 (some sources say 1919) in Bronx, New York. Bishop established himself as a nightclub comedian by the early 1950s, and was nicknamed The Frown Prince of Comedy for his cynical demeanor. It was during this time that he caught the attention of Frank Sinatra, who hired him as his opening act. Bishop started his television career performing standup comedy on the Cavalcade of Stars. He regularly appeared on the game show Keep Talking, and as a guest host for Jack Paar and Johnny Carson on the Tonight Show. In the 1960s, Bishop earned a spot in the Rat Pack, a group of entertainers comprising Frank Sinatra, Dean Martin, Sammy Davis, Jr., and Peter Lawford, who performed live in Las Vegas, Miami, Atlantic City, and Palm Springs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of material related to the career of comedian and actor Joey Bishop. The bulk of materials are related to the Joey Bishop Show (late night talk show) and include research files pertaining guests and potential guests, weekly line-ups, financial records, and guest contracts. Additionally there are a small number of scripts representing Bishop's appearances on other television programs. Notably absent are materials related to Bishop's film career and connection with the Rat Pack.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The series consist of materials documenting the production of the Joey Bishop Show talk show. The series is arranged into four subseries: 1. Guest research files; 2. Guest contracts; 3. Weekly lineups; 4. Financial records.

The Guest Research files include information about many of the guests (and potential guests) that appeared on the Joey Bishop talk show and may contain one or more of the following: one-page research synopsis, head shots, clippings, and publicity ephemera. The files are arranged alphabetically by last and/or group name.
The Weekly Lineup files may include rundowns, monologue material, notes/talking points related to guests, and cue cards. The files are arranged chronologically.
The Financial records comprise six ledgers: two ledgers labelled Joey Bishop Productions and four ledgers labelled accounts payable.

The Guest Contracts are Standard AFTRA Engagement Contracts for talent who appeared on the show. The contracts are arranged in a reverse chronological order by what appears to be the weekly air dates. The Guest Contracts are restricted and require advanced notice for use.
